<Layout title="Financial Advisors · Florida FA Partner Hub — Fiduciary RIA, Reg BI Broker-Dealer, 401(k) Loans, IRA First-Time Buyer &amp; Asset-Depletion Mortgage Coordination" description="Florida Financial Advisor partner hub educating buyers, sellers, and retirees on what FAs do in real estate: down payment funding strategy across liquid taxable account and retirement plan sources; 401(k) loan coordination under IRC Section 72(p) up to $50K or 50% vested balance with 15-year repayment for primary residence; IRA first-time home buyer withdrawal up to $10K per person penalty-exempt under IRC Section 72(t)(2)(F); Asset-Depletion mortgage qualifying on managed AUM portfolio balance amortized over 360 months; portfolio rebalancing post-purchase; estate planning alignment with property ownership structure (revocable trust vs individual vs joint); Florida homestead exemption under Florida Statutes Chapter 196 with creditor protection and descendant restrictions; SECURE Act 2.0 Required Minimum Distribution at age 73; federal estate tax exemption $13.99M (2025) sunsetting to approximately $7M in 2026 absent Congressional extension. FA types: Registered Investment Advisor (RIA) fiduciary practice under Investment Advisers Act of 1940; broker-dealer registered representative under SEC Regulation Best Interest (Reg BI) effective June 30, 2020; hybrid advisor with both RIA and BD registration; insurance-licensed advisor selling life insurance and annuity products; robo-advisor + human hybrid platforms (Schwab Intelligent Portfolios Premium, Vanguard Personal Advisor Services, Fidelity Personalized Planning, Betterment Premium, Wealthfront). FA designations: CFP Certified Financial Planner through CFP Board; CFA Chartered Financial Analyst through CFA Institute; ChFC Chartered Financial Consultant through The American College; CIMA Certified Investment Management Analyst through Investments and Wealth Institute; CRPC Chartered Retirement Planning Counselor; AIF Accredited Investment Fiduciary; Series 65 Investment Adviser Representative, Series 66 combined, Series 7 General Securities Representative through FINRA. PE consolidator wave including Hightower Advisors, Mercer Advisors, Wealth Enhancement Group, Captrust, Beacon Pointe, Creative Planning, Mariner Wealth Advisors, Edelman Financial Engines with practice valuations at 8-12x annual recurring revenue. Florida wealth migration accelerating FA practice growth. Dual partner-as-borrower CTA at bottom routing FAs to dedicated RIA principal mortgage guide (S-corp partnership W-2 + K-1 with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks under Fannie Mae B3-3.4-02) or wirehouse FA producer mortgage guide (multi-source variable income synthesis under B3-3.1-01)." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/financial-advisors/">
  <div class="pfa-scope" set:html={pfaBody} />
</Layout>

